to run a big organization like this
in place of her.

280
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,641
You have no idea.

281
00:22:33,769 --> 00:22:35,437
I invited her, so she can come and see.

282
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:36,813
To see it for herself how well

283
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,024
I ran the organization
that she threw away.

284
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:40,609
My bad.

285
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:43,153
She won't be able to see it with her eyes.

286
00:22:44,154 --> 00:22:45,822
My poor niece.

287
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:48,158
Yeon-seo won't be attending

288
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:49,409
the event tomorrow.

289
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:50,535
I invited her officially.

290
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:52,329
Let's make one thing clear.

291
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:53,622
We've fulfilled our duties.

292
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:54,790
Don't you just find this odd?

293
00:22:54,873 --> 00:22:56,291
It's been three years, you know.

294
00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:59,419
I was curious as to why she still
hasn't received a cornea donation.

295
00:22:59,669 --> 00:23:00,879
She's always so close.

296
00:23:01,379 --> 00:23:03,548
But it's always canceled
at the last minute.

297
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,760
Well, I guess the cells don't match.

298
00:23:06,927 --> 00:23:09,179
What can I do? That's her luck.

299
00:23:09,262 --> 00:23:10,097
Thanks to that,

300
00:23:10,388 --> 00:23:13,433
you managed to keep your position
as the General Director. Right?

301
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:18,480
What's your point?

302
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:22,859
It's interesting that someone's misfortune
can bring luck to someone.

303
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,950
