Blessed are those who have patience.

540
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:42,088
This foolish one
may not be aware of it now,

541
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:44,590
but she will appreciate you one day.

542
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:49,637
She will cry and regret her past actions.

543
00:39:52,598 --> 00:39:53,933
Give it to me. Where is it?

544
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:26,298
Yeon-seo!

545
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:30,845
I'm so glad that my niece is here!

546
00:40:33,514 --> 00:40:35,015
You two are in big trouble.

547
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:37,309
This foolish one has no patience for you.

548
00:40:39,311 --> 00:40:40,229
Watch out for her stick.

549
00:40:41,730 --> 00:40:43,107
Have you been well?

550
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:44,942
Of course.

551
00:40:45,317 --> 00:40:48,362
We've cried so much, wanting to see you.

552
00:40:49,155 --> 00:40:51,157
You never met us for the past three years.

553
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:52,408
But today, you're here.

554
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:55,035
Your parents must be proud of you.

555
00:40:55,327 --> 00:40:56,162
This is great.

556
00:40:56,412 --> 00:40:59,331
Our guests are very high-minded,

557
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,959
and they wanted to meet you.

558
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:03,919
You don't need to do anything.

559
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,839
That'll be better since you're pretty.
It will make you look more tragic.

560
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:09,341
The rich tend to spend money

561
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:11,760
when they feel a sense of superiority.

562
00:41:13,762 --> 00:41:15,097
Mom, that's enough.

563
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:17,600
Please understand.

564
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:20,144
As the General Director
of the ballet company,

565
00:41:20,227 --> 00:41:22,897
she's always thinking about sponsorships.

566
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:24,523
Ru-na.

567
00:41:26,817 --> 00:41:28,360
You remember my voice.

568
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:30,946
I'm glad you're here.

569
00:41:31,363 --> 00:41:32,239
Let's go in.

570
00:41:32,531 --> 00:41:35,868
Goodness, Ni-na will be exhilarated.

571
00:41:36,368 --> 00:41:39,622
She used to cry dozens of times a day
because she missed you.

572
00:41:40,247 --> 00:41:42,041
-Let's go inside.
-Let's go.

573
00:42:06,565 --> 00:42:08,275
Ni-na. Good luck.

574
00:42:09,401 --> 00:42:10,444
You can do it.

575
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:16,867
You're the best.

576
00:42:17,451 --> 00:42:19,161
The prima ballerina of Fantasia

577
00:42:19,828 --> 00:42:21,956
is only you, Ni-na.

578
00:42:22,581 --> 00:42:23,624
You're the star.

579
00:42:25,417 --> 00:42:26,877
-Isn't that Yeon-seo?
-Is it her?

580
00:42:30,381 --> 00:42:31,966
-She's really blind.
-It wasn't a rumor.

581
00:42:32,299 --> 00:42:33,634
-It was real.
-Goodness.

582
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:35,344
Poor girl.

583
00:42:37,596 --> 00:42:39,431
-My goodness.
-I feel terrible for her.

584
00:42:39,515 --> 00:42:40,641
Do you want to wait in the car?

585
00:42:41,267 --> 00:42:42,434
I need to go to the restroom.

586
00:42:44,687 --> 00:42:46,605
-It's on your left.
-I can go by myself.

587
00:42:46,981 --> 00:42:48,274
It's right around the corner.

588
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:49,900
You can go in first.

589
00:43:00,786 --> 00:43:02,746
Gosh. My handkerchief

590
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:21,015
-Hello.
-Goodness.

591
00:43:37,656 --> 00:43:39,783
No way. Yeon-seo is here?

592
00:43:39,992 --> 00:43:40,993
Did you see her?

593
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:42,870
Don't address her like that.

594
00:43:43,495 --> 00:43:44,997
She was once my idol.

595
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:46,790
Call her, "Ms. Lee."

596
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:48,459
By the way,

597
00:43:49,251 --> 00:43:52,296
I don't understand why she came
when she's blind.

598
00:43:52,671 --> 00:43:53,881
I hope she doesn't jinx any of us.

599
00:43:54,673 --> 00:43:55,799
The performance will begin soon.

600
00:43:55,883 --> 00:43:56,800
-Let's go.
-Okay.

601
00:43:56,884 --> 00:44:00,054
Please make your way to the theater.

602
00:47:44,778 --> 00:47:45,821
Yeon-seo.

603
00:47:47,864 --> 00:47:48,865
Yeon-seo

604
00:47:51,201 --> 00:47:53,537
Gosh, hello.

605
00:47:56,290 --> 00:47:57,749
How have you been, sir?

606
00:47:57,833 --> 00:47:59,167
I hope you've been well too, Odette.

607
00:47:59,251 --> 00:48:00,627
You get prettier every year.

608
00:48:02,713 --> 00:48:04,798
Hello, madam.

609
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:06,592
Hello, sir.

610
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:12,973
Where is the real Odette?

611
00:48:13,098 --> 00:48:15,100
I've been looking for her,
but I can't find her.

612
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:17,477
She'll be here soon.

613
00:48:17,644 --> 00:48:19,146
It's been three years, you know.

614
00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:21,690
Yeon-seo.

615
00:48:28,780 --> 00:48:31,491
Where is she?
The ceremony is about to start.

616
00:48:31,783 --> 00:48:33,660
Everyone, please raise your glasses.

617
00:48:33,744 --> 00:48:35,245
-What should we do?
-To celebrate the 20th

618
00:48:35,329 --> 00:48:36,913
anniversary of Fantasia
Cultural Foundation,

619
00:48:36,997 --> 00:48:38,123
we have invited a special guest.

620
00:48:38,206 --> 00:48:40,208
She's the only daughter
of the first chairman.

621
00:48:40,292 --> 00:48:42,794
Hey, we have to get him
to shut his mouth first.

622
00:48:43,128 --> 00:48:44,046
Go.

623
00:48:44,129 --> 00:48:45,922
We have invited Ms. Lee Yeon-seo.

624
00:48:47,633 --> 00:48:48,759
Give her a warm welcome.

625
00:48:49,968 --> 00:48:51,261
It's been three years.

626
00:48:51,345 --> 00:48:53,972
The daughter of Fantasia.
The madonna of Fantasia.

627
00:48:54,056 --> 00:48:57,017
Where are you, Ms. Lee Yeon-seo?

628
00:49:53,198 --> 00:49:55,117
Hello, I'm Lee Yeon-seo.

629
00:49:56,034 --> 00:49:57,661
Today is a special day.

630
00:49:58,078 --> 00:50:00,163
It's the 20th anniversary of Fantasia

631
00:50:00,747 --> 00:50:02,666
as well as my parents' death anniversary.

632
00:50:04,710 --> 00:50:06,753
I've given a lot of thought

633
00:50:06,962 --> 00:50:08,338
on how to celebrate this occasion.

634
00:50:09,172 --> 00:50:10,173
I thought about showing up

635
00:50:10,257 --> 00:50:11,967
as a corpse by hanging myself
in the restroom.

636
00:50:13,802 --> 00:50:14,803
To make a dramatic scene.

637
00:50:17,931 --> 00:50:20,308
I bet everyone is looking at me with pity.

638
00:50:21,768 --> 00:50:23,353
I hope that you can support us

639
00:50:23,770 --> 00:50:25,105
as much as you pity me

640
00:50:25,772 --> 00:50:27,566
and as much as you think
that I deserve this.

641
00:50:33,363 --> 00:50:36,450
As you know,
when I was the only principal dancer here,

642
00:50:36,783 --> 00:50:38,910
Keum Ni-na was my understudy.

643
00:50:38,994 --> 00:50:40,328
In other words, she was my shadow.

644
00:50:41,037 --> 00:50:42,581
If I got sick

645
00:50:42,664 --> 00:50:44,583
or ran away because I fell in love,

646
00:50:44,916 --> 00:50:47,002
her responsibility was to take my place.

647
00:50:47,753 --> 00:50:49,963
Unfortunately, I was too healthy.

648
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:52,215
And except ballet,
I found everything boring.

649
00:50:52,299 --> 00:50:54,634
I've never skipped a performance.

650
00:50:55,969 --> 00:50:58,305
However, when the sun is gone,
the moon is bound to dominate.

651
00:50:58,805 --> 00:51:01,099
As you all know, I've lost my eyesight.

652
00:51:01,183 --> 00:51:03,477
And Ni-na made a successful debut
as my replacement.

653
00:51:04,060 --> 00:51:05,896
When I was living in
darkness for three years,

654
00:51:06,354 --> 00:51:09,107
Ni-na has been shining
as Fantasia's prima ballerina.

655
00:51:09,983 --> 00:51:11,151
Isn't this story

656
00:51:11,818 --> 00:51:12,986
quite dramatic?

657
00:51:14,070 --> 00:51:15,864
Please support generously
to our ballet company,

658
00:51:16,364 --> 00:51:18,074
Fantasia, as much as you find

659
00:51:18,533 --> 00:51:20,076
this story entertaining

660
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:22,913
and as much as
you'll share it with others.

661
00:51:31,046 --> 00:51:32,339
I apologize for my long toast.

662
00:51:33,298 --> 00:51:34,633
Enjoy your day today.

663
00:51:34,883 --> 00:51:37,302
No one can be sure
if you'll be okay the next day.

664
00:51:46,061 --> 00:51:47,687
Let go. Let go of me.

665
00:51:51,233 --> 00:51:52,234
Ms. Choi!

666
00:51:52,317 --> 00:51:53,735
You've crossed the line.

667
00:51:54,152 --> 00:51:55,278
Get your hand off me.

668
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:59,199
I know that you are rude to the core

669
00:51:59,282 --> 00:52:01,034
and that you do everything you want to do

670
00:52:01,117 --> 00:52:02,619
like a spoiled princess.

671
00:52:03,119 --> 00:52:04,496
But this was just too much.

672
00:52:04,871 --> 00:52:07,999
You should've braced yourself when you had
a party on my parents' death anniversary.

673
00:52:10,001 --> 00:52:11,169
Those people inside

674
00:52:12,128 --> 00:52:13,839
are in the first percentile
of this country.

675
00:52:14,005 --> 00:52:15,966
Their seconds and minutes are like gold.

676
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:18,927
Do you think it's easy
to accommodate their schedules?

677
00:52:19,386 --> 00:52:20,971
What? You're laughing?

678
00:52:23,932 --> 00:52:24,808
Hey.

679
00:52:26,101 --> 00:52:27,853
Since we're at it, let's be frank here.

680
00:52:28,186 --> 00:52:30,313
How have we wronged you?

681
00:52:30,397 --> 00:52:31,523
What do you have against us

682
00:52:31,606 --> 00:52:33,400
to come all the way here
and ruin this event?

683
00:52:33,483 --> 00:52:34,818
You smiled.

684
00:52:38,530 --> 00:52:39,990
You smiled that day.

685
00:52:40,282 --> 00:52:41,283
Oh, no!

686
00:52:41,366 --> 00:52:42,450
Yeon-seo!

687
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:43,994
Yeon-seo!

688
00:52:57,299 --> 00:52:58,466
Goodness.

689
00:52:59,050 --> 00:53:00,051
Oh, my.

690
00:53:01,970 --> 00:53:03,013
You're unbelievable.

691
00:53:04,306 --> 00:53:06,391
I'm your aunt.

692
00:53:06,892 --> 00:53:08,184
Sure. You could say...

693
00:53:10,186 --> 00:53:14,065
that we're a distant cousin.

694
00:53:14,482 --> 00:53:16,484
But we're still a family.

695
00:53:17,527 --> 00:53:20,030
There's a line you can't cross.

696
00:53:21,114 --> 00:53:22,324
I thought you were just blind,

697
00:53:22,407 --> 00:53:24,284
but is it possible
that you've gone mad too?

698
00:53:25,619 --> 00:53:26,620
Stop.

699
00:53:28,997 --> 00:53:29,998
What if I don't?

700
00:53:30,332 --> 00:53:32,000
There will be a bigger scene.

701
00:53:38,924 --> 00:53:39,925
Let's go.

702
00:55:15,437 --> 00:55:16,604
You foolish one.

703
00:55:17,564 --> 00:55:19,649
The beautiful dance of your feet

704
00:55:20,316 --> 00:55:22,569
melted away the foul words
on the tip of your mouth.

705
00:55:24,112 --> 00:55:26,072
You should thank the one
who has given you that talent.

706
00:56:00,732 --> 00:56:02,067
It looks like the sun will set.

707
00:56:02,692 --> 00:56:04,069
The sunset glow is very beautiful.

708
00:56:05,195 --> 00:56:06,196
It's...

709
00:56:07,739 --> 00:56:09,115
very beautiful.

710
00:56:16,664 --> 00:56:17,999
Let's start getting ready slowly.

711
00:56:18,374 --> 00:56:19,667
You can begin your rehabilitation.

712
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:21,211
-And the foundation--
-Stop.

713
00:56:22,629 --> 00:56:23,505
Yeon-seo.

714
00:56:23,630 --> 00:56:25,298
I told you to stop calling me that!

715
00:56:26,132 --> 00:56:27,258
I hate everything!

716
00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:29,761
I hate ballet, the foundation, everything!

717
00:56:29,844 --> 00:56:31,596
So don't tell me what to do!

718
00:56:36,392 --> 00:56:37,477
Lee Yeon-seo!

719
00:56:39,521 --> 00:56:40,563
Did you

720
00:56:41,564 --> 00:56:42,857
just yell at me?

721
00:56:44,651 --> 00:56:45,735
Pull yourself together.

722
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:47,779
You're in the middle of a battlefield.

723
00:56:48,363 --> 00:56:50,448
Do you know how many guns
are pointed at your heart?

724
00:56:50,532 --> 00:56:53,159
No idea, but I hope
I can die at once, quickly.

725
00:56:53,493 --> 00:56:54,953
And stop saying that you want to die.

726
00:56:56,788 --> 00:56:57,872
We're almost there.

727
00:56:58,414 --> 00:57:01,042
If you give me just a little more time,

728
00:57:01,751 --> 00:57:03,419
I will bring you back to your place.

729
00:57:05,338 --> 00:57:06,464
My place?

730
00:57:07,298 --> 00:57:08,299
How?

731
00:57:08,716 --> 00:57:09,843
Are you going to give me eyes?

732
00:57:10,135 --> 00:57:11,386
-Yeon-seo.
-Bring me back?

733
00:57:11,636 --> 00:57:13,513
Where? Who says you can?
Who do you think you are?

734
00:57:14,222 --> 00:57:15,640
If you act like my dad once again,

735
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:17,684
I will really fire you.

736
00:58:02,187 --> 00:58:03,271
Mr. Cho.

737
00:58:13,781 --> 00:58:15,783
Yeon-seo. Yeon-seo, hold tight!

738
00:58:23,541 --> 00:58:25,919
What is it? What's going on?

739
00:58:26,586 --> 00:58:27,629
Yeon-seo.

740
00:58:46,606 --> 00:58:47,899
Gosh, I might be late.

741
00:58:48,441 --> 00:58:49,734
Mr. Cho...

742
00:59:27,272 --> 00:59:28,481
Mr. Cho.

743
00:59:30,316 --> 00:59:31,651
Can you hear me?

744
00:59:33,653 --> 00:59:34,862
Mr. Cho?

745
00:59:55,717 --> 00:59:57,343
Is anybody there?

746
01:00:00,638 --> 01:00:02,682
Help us.

747
01:00:05,685 --> 01:00:08,521
Who knew these flowers were for a funeral?

748
01:00:24,287 --> 01:00:25,163
Rest

749
01:00:26,247 --> 01:00:27,123
in peace.

750
01:00:31,794 --> 01:00:32,879
Who's there?

751
01:00:36,883 --> 01:00:37,759
Is...

752
01:00:39,344 --> 01:00:40,470
Is someone there?

753
01:00:43,389 --> 01:00:44,432
Over here.

754
01:00:44,974 --> 01:00:47,143
There are people here. Over here.

755
01:00:49,646 --> 01:00:50,521
Please.

756
01:00:51,105 --> 01:00:53,566
Please help us. Please.

757
01:00:57,320 --> 01:00:58,696
Hey, who are you?

758
01:00:59,572 --> 01:01:01,240
Are you a human or an animal?

759
01:01:03,326 --> 01:01:04,952
You jerk.

760
01:01:06,329 --> 01:01:07,622
Don't you have any conscience?

761
01:01:08,331 --> 01:01:09,957
If you ran away because you were scared,

762
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:12,460
make a report at least.

763
01:01:13,086 --> 01:01:14,003
Mister.

764
01:01:14,796 --> 01:01:16,255
Sir. Hey.

765
01:01:16,756 --> 01:01:19,133
Whoever you are, please.

766
01:01:21,135 --> 01:01:22,387
Why does her voice sound so clear?

767
01:01:40,029 --> 01:01:41,155
Help me.

768
01:01:42,115 --> 01:01:43,574
I can't.

769
01:01:43,950 --> 01:01:46,035
I really should not interfere
with the life of human beings.

770
01:01:46,953 --> 01:01:47,870
Please.

771
01:01:48,705 --> 01:01:49,831
Save me.

772
01:01:51,082 --> 01:01:53,710
I can't. I have no time. I have to go.

773
01:01:55,169 --> 01:01:56,337
I want to live.

774
01:01:58,715 --> 01:02:00,508
I wanted to die every single day,

775
01:02:02,468 --> 01:02:03,594
but I want to live now.

776
01:02:04,846 --> 01:02:06,097
I want to live.

777
01:02:10,893 --> 01:02:12,937
I wanted to die every single day,

778
01:02:15,481 --> 01:02:16,858
but I want to live now.

779
01:03:01,819 --> 01:03:02,653
I shouldn't

780
01:03:03,154 --> 01:03:04,614
have done that.

781
01:03:05,948 --> 01:03:06,783
I was not

782
01:03:07,658 --> 01:03:09,076
supposed to do that.

783
01:03:43,694 --> 01:03:44,695
Like smoke

784
01:03:45,738 --> 01:03:46,656
and dust.

785
01:03:48,950 --> 01:03:51,077
Hey, is someone there?

786
01:03:51,369 --> 01:03:52,578
Ms. Lee, were you dreaming?

787
01:03:53,996 --> 01:03:56,541
You must successfully
carry out a mission for 100 days

788
01:03:56,624 --> 01:03:58,334
for the door to reopen.

789
01:03:58,417 --> 01:04:00,920
Hello. I'm Kim Dan, the interviewee.

790
01:04:01,003 --> 01:04:02,088
I got closer to her.

791
01:04:03,422 --> 01:04:05,132
Why does a secretary
have to learn to do this?

792
01:04:05,216 --> 01:04:06,467
Make sure this place is spotless.

793
01:04:07,593 --> 01:04:09,095
What is my mission?

794
01:04:10,429 --> 01:04:11,347
Love.

795
01:04:11,514 --> 01:04:12,974
I will make you learn to love.

